question:
District category contains Dormitory District, and Restaurant District.
Supermarkets category contains Big Lots, Vons, and Sam's Club.
Product category contains Cheesecake, and Plant-based Milk.
Ingredient category contains Cardamom, and Cornmeal.
The number of each Restaurant District 's Big Lots equals 13.
The number of each Sam's Club 's Cheesecake equals each Dormitory District 's Big Lots.
The number of each Dormitory District 's Sam's Club equals each Big Lots 's Plant-based Milk.
The number of each Big Lots 's Plant-based Milk equals 6.
The number of each Restaurant District 's Sam's Club equals 7.
The number of each Big Lots 's Cheesecake equals 11.
The number of each Plant-based Milk 's Cornmeal equals 16.
The number of each Cheesecake 's Cardamom equals the sum of each Big Lots 's Plant-based Milk and each Sam's Club 's Plant-based Milk.
The number of each Vons 's Cheesecake equals 6 more than each Restaurant District 's Big Lots.
The number of each Restaurant District 's Vons equals 18 more than each Dormitory District 's Vons.
The number of each Dormitory District 's Vons equals 19.
The number of each Cheesecake 's Cornmeal equals each Big Lots 's Plant-based Milk.
The number of each Vons 's Plant-based Milk equals 1 times each Plant-based Milk 's Ingredient.
The number of each Dormitory District 's Big Lots equals the difference of each Big Lots 's Plant-based Milk and each Cheesecake 's Cardamom.
The number of each Sam's Club 's Plant-based Milk equals 19.
The number of each Plant-based Milk 's Cardamom equals 4 more than the sum of each Cheesecake 's Cardamom and each Restaurant District 's Vons.
How many Vons does Restaurant District have?
solution:
Define each Dormitory District 's Vons as D; So D = 19.
Define each Restaurant District 's Vons as i; So i = 18 + D = 18 + 19 = 14.
